text: Rodeo is a town in Contra Costa County, California. It is unincorporated. It is next to Hercules and the San Pablo Bay, in the San Francisco Bay Area. In 2020, 9,653 people lived in Rodeo. The town has an oil refinery. == References == Category:Census-designated places in California Category:Settlements in Contra Costa County, California
title: Rodeo, California
